The paper deals with off-policy evaluation in reinforcement learning, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on Markov decision processes (MDPs), which are a common framework for modeling decision-making problems in reinforcement learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are both likely categories. The paper also introduces a new estimator based on cross-fold estimation, which involves manipulating and analyzing data, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another possible category. Additionally, the paper deals with decision-making and control, which are topics that fall under the category of multi-agent systems, making cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with optimization and efficiency, which are topics that fall under the category of robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category as well.
